<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1862,2033]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,153,1907]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[259,388,1863,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cissuvorini">Cissuvorini</taxonomicName>
currently consists of 15 species in 5 genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A." box="[887,1181,1863,1889]" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="ref4831" refString="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A. (2017) Checklist of the Sesiidae of the world (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia). Available from: http: // www. sesiidae. net / Checklst. htm (accessed 23 March 2019)" type="url" year="2017">PÃ¼hringer &amp; Kallies 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Species of the genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,231,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,231,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[246,442,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[246,442,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[458,621,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,621,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Glossosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[678,821,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Dasysphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[678,821,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Dasysphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur mostly at the boundary between the Palaearctic and the Oriental regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[437,671,1935,1961]" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 569" refId="ref4916" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. In: Naumann, C. M. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera, 1, pp. 1 - 569, pls. 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1999">
Spatenka 
<emphasis box="[548,605,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies, A. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[682,921,1934,1961]" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="85 - 92" refId="ref4653" refString="Kallies, A. &amp; Arita, Y. (2005) Systematic position of the genus Dasysphecia (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae, Cissuvorini) with descrip- tions of two new bumble bee mimicking species from northern Vietnam. Transactions of the Lepidopterological Society of Japan, 56 (2), 85 - 92." type="journal article" year="2005">Kallies &amp; Arita 2005</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName authority="Engelhardt, 1946" authorityName="Engelhardt" authorityYear="1946" box="[1010,1327,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Cissuvora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1010,1124,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Cissuvora</emphasis>
Engelhardt, 1946
</taxonomicName>
, with one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Engelhardt 1946" authorityName="Engelhardt" authorityYear="1946" box="[245,683,1971,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Cissuvora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampelopsis">
<emphasis box="[245,490,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Cissuvora ampelopsis</emphasis>
Engelhardt 1946
</taxonomicName>
, occurs in North America (
<bibRefCitation author="Eichlin, T. D. &amp; Duckworth, W. D." box="[977,1284,1971,1997]" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="ref4522" refString="Eichlin, T. D. &amp; Duckworth, W. D. (1988) The Moths of America North of Mexico. Fascicle 5.1. Sesioidea, Sesiidae, Washington, 176 pp." type="book" year="1988">Eichlin &amp; Duckworth 1988</bibRefCitation>
). The biology of 
<taxonomicName box="[181,310,2007,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cissuvorini">Cissuvorini</taxonomicName>
is not well known. At present, the hostplants of only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[899,1039,2007,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romanovi">
<emphasis box="[899,1039,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">G. romanovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engelhardt" authorityYear="1946" box="[1092,1250,2007,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Cissuvora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampelopsis">
<emphasis box="[1092,1250,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">C. ampelopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known; both feed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[233,282,154,179]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Vitis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[233,282,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Vitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[295,398,153,180]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Vitaceae</taxonomicName>
). Most 
<taxonomicName box="[478,607,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cissuvorini">Cissuvorini</taxonomicName>
are poorly represented in collections. They seem to be attracted only rarely to artificial pheromone lures (
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies, A. &amp; Fukuzumi, K." box="[483,779,189,215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="133 - 134" refId="ref4709" refString="Kallies, A. &amp; Fukuzumi, K. (1998) First record of Toleria romanovi (Leech, 1889) (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae) from Aichi-ken, Honshu. Transactions of the lepidopterological Society of Japan, 49 (2), 133 - 134." type="journal article" year="1998">Kallies &amp; Fukuzumi 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, D." box="[790,943,189,215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="149 - 151" refId="ref4490" refString="Bartsch, D. (2003) Beitrag zur Glasfluglerfauna von Nepal (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift, 113 (5), 145, 149 - 151." type="journal article" year="2003">Bartsch 2003</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[961,1124,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[961,1124,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a well-developed proboscis and were found visiting flowers. In 
<collectingCountry box="[629,696,225,251]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler 1878)" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[707,1176,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contaminata">
<emphasis box="[707,1017,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia contaminata</emphasis>
(Butler 1878)
</taxonomicName>
is known to visit flowers of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thunberg) Gagn." authorityName="Gagn." baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" box="[224,642,261,288]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Cayratia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis box="[224,430,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Cayratia japonica</emphasis>
(Thunberg) Gagn.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[658,760,261,288]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Vitaceae</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Leech, 1889)" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[830,1275,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romanovi">
<emphasis box="[830,1107,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia romanovi</emphasis>
(Leech, 1889)
</taxonomicName>
was observed visiting flowers of 
<taxonomicName authority="Aiton" authorityName="Aiton" box="[365,648,297,323]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" genus="Ligustrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lucidum">
<emphasis box="[365,578,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Ligustrum lucidum</emphasis>
Aiton
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Hoffmannsegg &amp; Link" authorityYear="1809" box="[663,769,297,324]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Oleaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thunb.) Koidz." authorityName="Koidz." baseAuthorityName="Thunb." box="[832,1291,297,324]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Kalopanax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="septemlobus">
<emphasis box="[832,1101,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Kalopanax septemlobus</emphasis>
(Thunb.) Koidz.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Durande" authorityYear="1782" box="[1305,1428,297,324]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Araliaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Sugiura, S. &amp; Sakagami, K. &amp; Hayashi, M." box="[159,379,333,359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="13 - 16" refId="ref4877" refString="Sugiura, S., Sakagami, K. &amp; Hayashi, M. (2019) Flower-visiting clearwing moths in the Oki Islands, Japan. Lepidoptera Science, 70 (1), 13 - 16." type="journal article" year="2019">
Sugiura 
<emphasis box="[255,304,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[428,498,333,359]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wang &amp; Yang, 2002)" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Yang" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[509,1021,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[509,768,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia sinensis</emphasis>
(Wang &amp; Yang, 2002)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1028,1157,333,359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">comb.Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­nov.</emphasis>
was found on flowers of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[151,224,369,395]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Cissus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,224,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Cissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[269,369,369,396]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Vitaceae</taxonomicName>
) (Kallies, personal observation). Most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[921,1001,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[921,1001,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a rudimentary proboscis and thus are unlikely to feed, making them less likely to be detected. The precise relationship between 
<taxonomicName box="[1196,1325,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cissuvorini">Cissuvorini</taxonomicName>
and other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[151,244,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sesiidae</taxonomicName>
is currently unclear. The tribe clearly shows affinities to both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[940,1016,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Sesiini">Sesiini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[1071,1225,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Paranthrenini">Paranthrenini</taxonomicName>
, but more work, in particular a molecular phylogeny, is required to resolve its precise position in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[1014,1107,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sesiidae</taxonomicName>
and determine whether it can be maintained a valid tribe (
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M." box="[464,640,513,539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref4758" refString="Naumann, C. M. (1971) Untersuchungen zur Systematik und Phylogenese der holarktischen Sesiiden (Insecta, Lepidoptera). Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 1, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="1971">Naumann 1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[652,885,513,539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 569" refId="ref4916" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. In: Naumann, C. M. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera, 1, pp. 1 - 569, pls. 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1999">
Spatenka 
<emphasis box="[762,818,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="124" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,153,1907]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[323,466,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Dasysphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[323,466,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Dasysphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is relatively well known. It was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies, A. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[956,1212,548,575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="85 - 92" refId="ref4653" refString="Kallies, A. &amp; Arita, Y. (2005) Systematic position of the genus Dasysphecia (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae, Cissuvorini) with descrip- tions of two new bumble bee mimicking species from northern Vietnam. Transactions of the Lepidopterological Society of Japan, 56 (2), 85 - 92." type="journal article" year="2005">Kallies &amp; Arita (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, who described two new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[357,455,585,611]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, bringing the number of currently known species to three. However, additional species are known to the authors showing that the genus occurs from the foothills of the Himalaya Mts in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1379,1437,621,647]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">India</collectingCountry>
throughout 
<collectingCountry box="[282,352,657,683]" name="Nepal" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[467,537,657,683]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[548,659,657,683]" name="Myanmar" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[670,770,657,683]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[927,1022,657,683]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(manuscript in preparation). Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[181,324,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Dasysphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,324,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Dasysphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by their bumblebee-like appearance, their forewing venation (R4, R5 stalked) and their female genitalia (corpus bursae small, simple, without signum).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,153,1907]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[322,485,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,485,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by two well-known species in 
<collectingCountry box="[994,1061,765,791]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Japan</collectingCountry>
, several species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1275,1342,765,791]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
and one in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,251,801,827]" name="Nepal" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Nepal</collectingCountry>
. Until recently, it was considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Spatenka et al. 1999)" authorityName="Spatenka" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Spatenka" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[794,1133,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[794,874,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[889,1125,801,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 569" refId="ref4916" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. In: Naumann, C. M. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera, 1, pp. 1 - 569, pls. 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1999">
Spatenka 
<emphasis box="[1001,1057,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; however, it was treated as a valid genus by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O." box="[338,625,837,863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="14" refId="ref4400" refString="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O. (1998) A Revision of Embrik Strand's Clearwing Moth Types (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae) from Taiwan. Chinese Journal of Entomology, 18 (3), 14 1 - 165." type="journal article" year="1998">Arita &amp; Gorbunov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
and subsequent authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A." box="[906,1198,837,863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref4791" refString="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A. (2004). Provisional check list of the Sesiidae of the world (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia). Mitteilungen der Entomologischen Arbeitsgemeinschaft Salzkammergut, 4, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2004">PÃ¼hringer &amp; Kallies 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A." box="[1208,1267,837,863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" refId="ref4831" refString="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A. (2017) Checklist of the Sesiidae of the world (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia). Available from: http: // www. sesiidae. net / Checklst. htm (accessed 23 March 2019)" type="url" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies, A." box="[1278,1425,837,863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="387 - 396" refId="ref4608" refString="Kallies, A. (2007) A revision of the clearwing moth species described by Zukowsky from China with additional notes on Sesiidae species from the Mell collection (Sesiidae). Nota lepidopterological, 30 (2), 387 - 396." type="journal article" year="2007">Kallies 2007</bibRefCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[325,405,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,405,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the venation (R4, R5 stalked in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[826,989,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,989,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, R4, R5 arising separately from R 
<quantity box="[1392,1436,873,899]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[151,231,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,231,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the presence of a well-developed proboscis (reduced in 
<taxonomicName box="[881,961,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[881,961,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the morphology of the female antennae (simple in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[316,479,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[316,479,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, serrate in 
<taxonomicName box="[603,683,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[603,683,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[774,917,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Dasysphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[774,917,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Dasysphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by the well-developed proboscis, the wasp-like appearance and the female genitalia (corpus bursae larger, with a well-developed signum and multiple transverse folds). Our study of the Asian 
<taxonomicName box="[605,734,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cissuvorini">Cissuvorini</taxonomicName>
and examination of the relevant 
<typeStatus box="[1098,1146,1017,1043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">type</typeStatus>
material showed that 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Yang, 2002" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Cissuvora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Cissuvora sinensis</emphasis>
Wang &amp; Yang, 2002
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[808,971,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[808,971,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Glossosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[988,1117,1053,1079]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">comb.Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­nov.</emphasis>
) and is closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Glossosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contaminata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">G. contaminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(manuscript in preparation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,153,1907]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[325,405,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,405,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently consists of only two species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, [1865]" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[855,1197,1124,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abiaeformis">
<emphasis box="[855,871,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[886,1020,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">abiaeformis</emphasis>
Walker, [1865]
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Arita &amp; Gorbunov, 2001" authorityName="Arita &amp; Gorbunov" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilana">
<emphasis box="[1253,1269,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1284,1342,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">ilana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gorbunov, O. &amp; Arita, Y." pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="9 - 51" refId="ref4558" refString="Gorbunov, O. &amp; Arita, Y. (2001) A revision of Felix Bryk's clearing [sic] moth types (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae), at the Naturhistoriska Riksmuseet in Stockholm, Sweden. Melittia, a lepidopterological almanac, 1, 9 - 51." type="journal article" year="2001">Arita &amp; Gorbunov, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which occur in eastern mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[708,775,1161,1187]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
and on 
<collectingCountry box="[860,945,1161,1187]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, respectively. However, our studies revealed that the concept of 
<taxonomicName box="[366,446,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[366,446,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
required revision and the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[879,1076,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[879,1076,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1092,1190,1197,1223]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">syn.Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­rev.</emphasis>
) as a younger subjective synonym, a view consistent with that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[643,890,1233,1259]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 569" refId="ref4916" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. In: Naumann, C. M. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera, 1, pp. 1 - 569, pls. 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1999">
Spatenka 
<emphasis box="[752,807,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">et al.</emphasis>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O." box="[898,1183,1233,1259]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="14" refId="ref4400" refString="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O. (1998) A Revision of Embrik Strand's Clearwing Moth Types (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae) from Taiwan. Chinese Journal of Entomology, 18 (3), 14 1 - 165." type="journal article" year="1998">Arita &amp; Gorbunov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a valid genus based on the constitution of forewing radial veins. Notably, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[1073,1270,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1270,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from female specimens. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName box="[558,638,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[558,638,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well know from male specimens, the genitalia of which were studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M." box="[187,378,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref4758" refString="Naumann, C. M. (1971) Untersuchungen zur Systematik und Phylogenese der holarktischen Sesiiden (Insecta, Lepidoptera). Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 1, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="1971">Naumann (1971)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[434,687,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 569" refId="ref4916" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. In: Naumann, C. M. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera, 1, pp. 1 - 569, pls. 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1999">
Spatenka 
<emphasis box="[545,602,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">et al.</emphasis>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
. The latter authors also provided figures of the female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,313,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abiaeformis">
<emphasis box="[151,313,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">T. abiaeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it was unclear whether they indeed belonged to this species. The collection of a small series of clearly conspecific typical male and female 
<taxonomicName box="[640,720,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,720,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1090,1413,1439]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
, similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[1212,1373,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abiaeformis">
<emphasis box="[1212,1373,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">T. abiaeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs 7, 8), has now allowed us to reassess the validity 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[709,905,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[709,905,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O." box="[1072,1365,1449,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="14" refId="ref4400" refString="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O. (1998) A Revision of Embrik Strand's Clearwing Moth Types (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae) from Taiwan. Chinese Journal of Entomology, 18 (3), 14 1 - 165." type="journal article" year="1998">Arita &amp; Gorbunov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, R3 is separate from R 
<quantity box="[329,371,1485,1511]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[377,457,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[377,457,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while it branches off R 
<quantity box="[724,766,1485,1511]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[772,968,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[772,968,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Close examination of the forewing venation of our 
<taxonomicName box="[280,360,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,360,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens shows that R3 branches off R 
<quantity box="[830,873,1521,1547]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
exactly the position shown by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O." pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="14" refId="ref4400" refString="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O. (1998) A Revision of Embrik Strand's Clearwing Moth Types (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae) from Taiwan. Chinese Journal of Entomology, 18 (3), 14 1 - 165." type="journal article" year="1998">Arita &amp; Gorbunov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Strand" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[277,421,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegerides">
<emphasis box="[277,421,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">C. aegerides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[481,529,1557,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[661,857,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[661,857,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The branch point, however, is weakly sclerotized and may thus have been overlooked by these authors. The male genitalia represent the classic 
<taxonomicName box="[1212,1292,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1212,1292,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphology (
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M." box="[159,336,1629,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref4758" refString="Naumann, C. M. (1971) Untersuchungen zur Systematik und Phylogenese der holarktischen Sesiiden (Insecta, Lepidoptera). Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 1, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="1971">Naumann 1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Spatenka, K. &amp; Gorbunov, O. &amp; Lastuvka, Z. &amp; Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[350,588,1629,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 569" refId="ref4916" refString="Spatenka, K., Gorbunov, O., Lastuvka, Z., Tosevski, I. &amp; Arita, Y. (1999) Sesiidae - Clearwing Moths. In: Naumann, C. M. (Ed.), Handbook of Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera, 1, pp. 1 - 569, pls. 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1999">
Spatenka 
<emphasis box="[461,519,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
), the female genitalia are very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Strand" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[1143,1286,1629,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegerides">
<emphasis box="[1143,1286,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">C. aegerides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1947" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colochelyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">C. colochelyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O." box="[298,575,1665,1691]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="14" refId="ref4400" refString="Arita, Y. &amp; Gorbunov, O. (1998) A Revision of Embrik Strand's Clearwing Moth Types (Lepidoptera: Sesiidae) from Taiwan. Chinese Journal of Entomology, 18 (3), 14 1 - 165." type="journal article" year="1998">Arita &amp; Gorbunov 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorbunov, O. &amp; Arita, Y." box="[587,863,1665,1691]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="9 - 51" refId="ref4558" refString="Gorbunov, O. &amp; Arita, Y. (2001) A revision of Felix Bryk's clearing [sic] moth types (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae), at the Naturhistoriska Riksmuseet in Stockholm, Sweden. Melittia, a lepidopterological almanac, 1, 9 - 51." type="journal article" year="2001">Gorbunov &amp; Arita 2001</bibRefCitation>
). In particular, the shape of the signum, the folded structure of the bursa copulatrix, the ring-shaped antrum, the sclerotized ridge at the base of the ductus seminalis and the reduced sclerotized anterior margin of segment 8 are very similar to 
<emphasis box="[1017,1167,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Strand" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[1017,1163,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegerides">C. aegerides</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Thus, we conclude that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[151,348,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chimaerosphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,348,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Chimaerosphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[706,786,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[706,786,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which contains five species, all of which are known from mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[262,329,1809,1835]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[381,467,1809,1835]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. Our analyses of the newly discovered specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1179,1809,1835]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1286,1809,1835]" name="Laos" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Laos</collectingCountry>
revealed that they belong to an undescribed species that should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[882,962,1845,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[882,962,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We here described this species as 
<taxonomicName authority="Ogane &amp; Kallies" authorityName="Ogane &amp; Kallies" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Toleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aritai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Toleria aritai</emphasis>
Ogane &amp; Kallies
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[416,530,1881,1907]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">spec.Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­Â­nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
